          Introduction to Cybersecurity & Linux Basics.md
(The CIA Triad and Common Cybersecurity Threats).md

The CIA Triad: A Pillar of Cybersecurity.md
The CIA Triad is a fundamental model in cybersecurity that ensures data protection and system integrity. It stands for Confidentiality, Integrity, and Availability, which are the three key principles of cybersecurity.md

Confidentiality.md 
Confidentiality ensures that sensitive information is accessible only to authorized users.md 

Integrity.md
Integrity protects data from being altered or corrupted.md 

Availability.md
Availability ensures that data and systems remain accessible when needed.md

Cyber Threats:.md
Some common cyber threats include;.md
Phishing.md
 In phishing, attackers trick users into giving away personal information through fake emails or websites.md 
Prevention.md
- Verify email senders before clicking on links.md
- Avoid downloading attachments from unknown sources.md
- Use email security filters and anti-phishing tools.md

Malware.md 
A malware is any malicious software that can damage or steal data.md 
Prevention.md
- Keep software and operating systems updated.md
- Install reputable antivirus and anti-malware programs.md
- Avoid downloading software from unverified sources.md

Ransomware.md 
This is a type of malware that locks users out of their files until a ransom is paid. These threats exploit human error and system vulnerabilities, making cybersecurity awareness and strong security measures essential.md
Prevention.md
- Back Up Your Files – Save important files on an external hard drive or cloud storage so you don’t lose them if attacked.md
- Avoid Suspicious Links & Emails.md
Use Strong Security Software – Install a good antivirus and keep it updated to detect and block threats.md
- Always update your computer and software to fix security weaknesses hackers might exploit.md
- Don’t Download from Unknown Sources.md

